<div id="content_table" style="width: 866px;"   >
<br><br>
<h1 class="h1_blue_dark">How to Start an Essay</h1>


  
<table width="866px" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" cellpadding="5" border=0>
<tr><td>
<div>
<h1 class="h1_gray">Introduction</h1>
<br>
One of the biggest challenges in writing a paper is coming up with ideas.  Your instructor may have given you a 
general topic to work with, but how can you narrow that topic?  Once narrowed, how do you come up with ideas for 
your paper?  Do you even know what you believe or feel about the topic?  To help you overcome these common obstacles, 
this workshop will focus on the prewriting stage of the writing process and give you strategies you can use to generate 
ideas for your writing projects.<br><br>

</div>
</td></tr>


<tr><td><table width="866px" class="border_green" border=0>
	<tr>
	<td><div>

<strong>By the end of this activity, you should be able to:</strong> <br><br>
	<ul class="c">
		<li>Explain the importance of the prewriting stage of the writing process</li>
		<li>Describe various prewriting strategies (asking questions, brainstorming, clustering, freewriting, talking it out)</li>
		<li>Select and apply prewriting strategies to writing tasks</li>
	</ul>
</div>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table></td></tr>

<tr><td><div>
<br><br>
<h1 class="h1_gray">Let's get started!</h1><br>

<strong>If at any time you need help please ask a tutor.</strong><br><br>
</div></td></tr>
<!-- this is the steps table -->
<tr><td>
<table width="866px" border=0>
<tr><td width="80px" valign="top"><h1 class="h1_gray">Step 1: </h1></td>
<td valign="bottom"><div>First you'll need to make sure you have the handouts for this activity. 
If you don't, ask a tutor to help you.<br><br></div></td></tr>

<tr><td width="80px" valign="top"><h1 class="h1_gray">Step 2: </h1></td>
<td><div>Once you have the handouts in front of you, view this 
<a href="Prewriting Strategies.pptx">PowerPoint</a> presentation.  
<br><br></div></td></tr>

<tr><td width="80px" valign="top"><h1 class="h1_gray">Step 3: </h1></td>
<td><div>Complete the activities in the worksheet. NOTE:  Some exercises require that you work with a partner to do a role-play. Please ask a 
tutor to be your partner for those exercises.
<br><br>
STOP and review your worksheet with a tutor.
<br><br></div></td></tr>

<tr><td width="80px" valign="top"><h1 class="h1_gray">Step 4: </h1></td>
<td><div>Complete the self-reflection in the handouts.<br><br>
</div></td></tr>

<tr><td width="80px" valign="top"><h1 class="h1_gray">Step 5: </h1></td>
<td><div>Review your work with a tutor.<br><br>
</div></td></tr>

</table>
</td></tr>
         
<tr><td><div>

<h1 class="h1_gray">That's it. You are done! Thank you for completing this guided learning activity.</h1>
</div></td></tr>                  
                  



